That&#39;s not actually *Razor Pages*. It&#39;s the old [ASP.NET Web Pages][1] framework. If you have a choice and are learning, I would recommend [Razor Pages][2] over Web Pages, which hasn&#39;t been developed for about 7 years, now.

Whether Web Pages or Razor Pages, the issue you have is likely the same. When you include scripts in a specific page, you should do so in an `@section` name &quot;scripts&quot;. That way, it will be included in the layout page AFTER library scripts, which should be included before the `RenderSection(&quot;scripts&quot;)` call in the layout page:

    @using WebMatrix.Data;
    
    @{
    Layout = &quot;../Shared/Index.cshtml&quot;;
    }
    
    @section scripts{
    &lt;script&gt;
        Ext.create(&#39;Ext.Container&#39;, {
            fullscreen: true,
            padding: 10,
            items: {
                xtype: &#39;button&#39;,
                text: text,
                handler: handler
            }
        });
    &lt;/script&gt;
    }


  [1]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/web-pages/overview/getting-started/introducing-aspnet-web-pages-2/getting-started
  [2]: https://www.learnrazorpages.com

